## API Details

### `MappedInputFile`

New method added alongside existing `readRange`:

```java
/// Returns a read-only MemorySegment slice of the mmap'd file region.
/// Zero-copy for whole-file mode (≤ 2 GB); maps the region on demand
/// for per-region mode (> 2 GB).
///
/// The returned segment is valid for the lifetime of the provided Arena.
/// Callers must not close the Arena while any thread is reading from the segment.
///
/// @param arena  the Arena that owns the returned segment's lifetime
/// @param offset byte offset within the file
/// @param length number of bytes to map
/// @return a read-only MemorySegment of exactly `length` bytes
public MemorySegment readRangeAsSegment(Arena arena, long offset, int length) throws IOException
```

### `LibdeflateDecompressor`

Already added in #354:

```java
/// Decompresses GZIP data from a MemorySegment into a thread-local native
/// output buffer. No heap copy. Caller must consume the result before the
/// next call on the same thread.
public MemorySegment decompressToSegment(MemorySegment input, long compressedSize,
                                          int uncompressedSize) throws IOException
```

### `NativePlainDecoder` and `NativeBssDecoder`

Already added in #354. Both implement `ValueDecoder` and accept a `MemorySegment` instead of `byte[]`.

