## Tests

### Correctness tests

- Existing page decode tests must pass unchanged on both Java 21 and Java 22 paths
- Add `NativePlainDecoderTest` and `NativeBssDecoderTest` covering:
  - Required columns (dense, `definitionLevels == null`)
  - Nullable columns (sparse, mixed null/non-null)
  - All numeric types: `INT32`, `INT64`, `FLOAT`, `DOUBLE`
  - Boundary conditions: single value, empty page, full page
- Add `MappedInputFileSegmentTest` for `readRangeAsSegment`:
  - Whole-file mode (≤ 2 GB)
  - Per-region mode (> 2 GB) — can use `MappedInputFileLargeFileTest` infrastructure
  - Out-of-bounds access throws `IndexOutOfBoundsException`

### Benchmarks (required before merge)

A new performance test `NativeDecodePerformanceTest` in `dev.hardwood.perf`:

- Two contenders: heap path (PlainDecoder / ByteStreamSplitDecoder on byte[])
  vs native path (NativePlainDecoder / NativeBssDecoder on MemorySegment)
- GZIP-compressed numeric columns (DOUBLE, FLOAT, PLAIN and BYTE_STREAM_SPLIT encodings)
- Same warmup + timed run structure, configurable via system properties
- Correctness verified by comparing column sums between contenders
- Pass criteria: native path must show measurable improvement in rows/sec
  and MB/sec to jutify Java-version-split.